Al,

In reading your posting, and in the reference to oils, I have been
considering going to a semi sythetic oil.

I have several motorcycles, and what better a test for oil break-down
than an air cooled bike?

They fry sitting at stop lights, durring the summer month's, and usually
are run pretty hard and long, way beyond the mfg's intented design.

I have been using an oil from Specto Oil company, after reading an oil
test by Motorcycle Consumer New's, a by-monthy publication.
They have zero allegance to any manufacter, as they have no advertising,
and aren't afraid to give negative veiw's on any product they test.

Anyway, the Oils from Spectro Oli co. surpassed the rest tested (
Castrol, Bel-Ray, Mobi One, etc.) in every catagory.( shear stength,
temp break down, viscosity loss, etc.)

Anyhow, I'm going to start using this stuff in my air cooled bus, it
tested good, it seems to stand up to my abusive driving habit's while
I'm on my air cooled ( liquid cooled also) bike's, and it can't hurt
giving it a shot----anything has got to help in the engine longevity
dept.!! :>)

